msgstr ""

#: ../../source/exploring_catalog_and_datasets/04_getting_involved/following_dataset_updates.rst:7
msgid "Only authenticated users can follow a dataset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/exploring_catalog_and_datasets/04_getting_involved/following_dataset_updates.rst:9
msgid ""
"If you have an OpenDataSoft account, log in. Once logged in, the Follow "
"button becomes clickable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/exploring_catalog_and_datasets/04_getting_involved/following_dataset_updates.rst:10
msgid ""
"If you do not have an OpenDataSoft account, and if the portal allows "
"anonymous users to create an OpenDataSoft account, sign up to the portal. "
"Once signed up and logged in, the Follow button becomes clickable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/exploring_catalog_and_datasets/04_getting_involved/following_dataset_updates.rst:11
msgid ""
"If you do not have an OpenDataSoft account, and if the portal doesn't allow "
"anonymous users to sign up, the Follow button will not be displayed in the "
"Information tab of any dataset, and you won't have the possiblity to follow "
"a dataset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/exploring_catalog_and_datasets/04_getting_involved/following_dataset_updates.rst:13
msgid ""
"Users have the possibility to follow datasets they are particularly "
"interested in, to be informed whenever the dataset is modified. The \"follow"
" dataset\" feature is especially convenient for those whose creation (mobile"
" application, website, academic paper etc.) relies on the data contained in "
"a dataset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/exploring_catalog_and_datasets/04_getting_involved/following_dataset_updates.rst:15
msgid "To follow a dataset:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/exploring_catalog_and_datasets/04_getting_involved/following_dataset_updates.rst:17
msgid "Go to the Information tab of the chosen dataset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/exploring_catalog_and_datasets/04_getting_involved/following_dataset_updates.rst:18
msgid "Click on the Follow button under the dataset metadata."
msgstr ""
